  "text": "Controllability above the thresholds. It is natural to analyze which initial conditions can still be brought to 0 or θ, when L L . Let us give a simple negative result in this direction. To answer the question, the multiplicity of stationary solutions is critical and there are many results [CITATION_1] . Generally, these solutions are ordered, and thus, the maximal one will attract all initial conditions that are uniformly above it, by the comparison principle and Matano's theorem. Going more deeply would require to analyze the basin of attraction of each stationary solution.",
